comments: Davis (LAL) is drawn into the air toward Mobley (CLE) and comes down into Mobley, delivering contact that alters his layup attempt at the basket.
Strus' (CLE) right arm briefly comes around James' (LAL) leg as he navigates over the pick and the marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
James (LAL) firms up in Strus' (CLE) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Mitchell (CLE) avoids making illegal contact with James (LAL) during the layup attempt at the basket.
Christie (LAL) slides his hand off of Strus (CLE) as he attempts to relocate after setting the pick and the contact is marginal.
Reaves (LAL) retreats in Mitchell's (CLE) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the drive around the perimeter.
Davis (LAL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Mobley (CLE) lowers his hand toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with James' (LAL) lower body during the dunk attempt at the basket.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Allen (CLE) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs with Reaves (LAL) as he defends over the screen.
Strus (CLE) establishes himself in Christie's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Mitchell's (CLE) off-arm comes out slightly as he releases away from Reaves (LAL) and the contact at the end of the drive is marginal.
Prince (LAL) establishes himself in Mobley's (CLE) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Strus (CLE) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Reaves (LAL) brings his hand to the ball and deflects it away from Mobley (CLE) during the rebounding opportunity. The body contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Christie (LAL) legally contests Mitchell's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Allen (CLE) firms up over his left leg and marginal contact occurs as Christie (LAL) moves into and around the screen.
Mitchell's (CLE) right forearm comes out slightly as he ends his dribble drive and marginal contact occurs with Christie (LAL).
Allen (CLE) comes across Reaves' (LAL) arm and body, which impacts Reaves' ability to return to the floor normally during the rebounding opportunity.
Reaves (LAL) ventures fully beyond the three-point line between free throw attempts.
Reaves (LAL) moves alongside LeVert's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs as LeVert changes direction during the drive.
Prince's (LAL) left hand brushes LeVert's (CLE) front after the gather and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
